类 PokemonTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • PokemonTable
  • 所有已实现的接口:
    Manager, MapADT
    public class PokemonTable
extends java.lang.Object
implements MapADT, Manager
    This class intends to hash the organized data into its own hash table and install some basic operations to allow the table adjustments which will be the important prerequisites for the front end developing. To get more abundant operations, the Manager interface is implemented.
    版本:
    1.0
    作者:
    Tianwei Bao, Seungjun Chong, Minghao Zhou, Liangqi Cai, Zhiwei Cao, Jiahe Jin, Yunzhao Liu

    • 方法详细资料

      • rehashing

        private void rehashing()
        The private rehashing() method is a helper method which intends to check if the load factor is attained. If it is accomplished that load capacity is greater or equal to 80%, starting it.

      • hashKey

        private int hashKey​(java.lang.Object key)
        The hashKey(Object key) is the helper method trying to get the hashed key by the absolute key.hashcode() mod capacity.
        参数:
        key - the KeyType user entered.
        返回:
        the index of hashtable.

      • getTypes

        public void getTypes()

      • put

        public boolean put​(java.lang.Object name,
                   java.lang.Object pokemon)
        This method intends to put the Pokemon into the hashTable with its name as the key, at the index corresponding to the hashed key by the .getHashKey() method. Before adding the Pokemon, we need to check if the name of pokemon has already existed by using .containsKey() method. When the added pokemon makes the hashtable attains its load capacity (larger or equal than 0.75), we need to rehash the table and double its capacity. Remember, the size is the number of pokemon being added, and it is recommended to use the private rehashing method to help double the hashtable's capacity.
        指定者:
        put 在接口中 MapADT
        参数:
        name - the name of the Pokemon as the key
        pokemon - the Pokemon class Object as the value
        返回:
        true if we successfully add the pokemon in our table, and false if the table does not change.
